Program: Outlook
Title: 23/08/2010
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0095xr9
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 24 Aug 2010
SISTERS IN THE COMBAT ZONE John Witmer's family hit the headlines in America in 2003 when his three daughters all joined the forces to serve in Iraq. Twins Charity and Michelle and their older sister Rachel were deployed to Baghdad in March 2003. In 2004 Michelle became the first female US solider to be killed in conflict. Six years later, John is still dealing with his daughter's death. RETURN TO KABUL Meena Baktash from the BBC's Pashto and Dari Service grew up in the Afghan capital, Kabul, in the 1970s. Like any teenager she spent those years dreaming of her future. She left the country in the early nineties and became a journalist. Now she has returned to Kabul to find out how her family has been affected by years of conflict. Show less